‚à´‚à´_Q |œâ(x,t)|^p ¬∑ [1 ‚àí Œì(x,t)]^q dx dt < ‚àû

where p, q satisfy scaling invariance constraints. The geometric content: regions where Œæ is coherent (Œì small) allow weaker integrability requirements on |œâ|; incoherent Œæ requires stronger magnitude control.

