execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/near-beltrami-pressure-perturbation.md:10:For flows epsilon-close to Beltrami (u = u_B + epsilon v), the pressure decomposes into a "Beltrami part" (CZ-lossless, -|u|^2/2) and a "deficit part" (CZ-lossy, O(epsilon)). The degradation from exact Beltrami is **continuous and linear in epsilon** ‚Äî there is no threshold discontinuity.
