execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/near-beltrami-pressure-perturbation.md:44:**RESOLVED by E007:** The Beltrami deficit B_k = ||curl(u_below) - lambda_opt u_below||_{L^2} / ||u_below||_{L^2} scales as O(2^{-k}) for ABC flows. The truncation perturbation is confined to the shrinking set where |u| > lambda_k. The pressure remainder fraction R_frac = O(2^{-k}) and the bottleneck remainder I_r/I_t = O(2^{-k}). The mechanism survives truncation. See `vasseur-de-giorgi/beltrami-deficit-truncation-survival.md` and `vasseur-de-giorgi/pressure-bernoulli-dominance-truncated.md` for full measurements.
