execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:34:### Vasseur De Giorgi Framework (vasseur-pressure E001, E003, E004, E005, E008)
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:35:- **[vasseur-de-giorgi/](vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md)** ‚Äî Vasseur's 2007 De Giorgi approach to NS regularity. Beta is a recurrence exponent (NOT pressure integrability). Beta > 3/2 implies full regularity (Conjecture 14). Current beta < 4/3, bottleneck is a single non-divergence pressure term `P_k^{21}`. DNS measurement approaches defined and TESTED. DNS results: all beta_eff < 4/3 (max 1.01 for ABC); bottleneck exponent gamma DECREASES with Re (gap is genuine); ABC/Beltrami flow uniquely favorable. CZ slack for `P_k^{21}` is k-INDEPENDENT (FALSIFIES CZ improvement hypothesis). `P21` has LESS CZ slack than full pressure. Tran-Yu Galilean invariance program ORTHOGONAL. Pressure Poisson equation Galilean-invariant for div-free flows. Choi-Vasseur 2014 three-way decomposition (beta=7/6, does NOT bypass bottleneck). Post-2007 landscape: NO paper has improved beta beyond 4/3. Fernandez-Dalgo 2025 dynamic pressure (epsilon-regularity, not De Giorgi). Vasseur-Yang 2021 vorticity De Giorgi: pressure eliminated, but universal 4/3 barrier from trilinear form. H^1 pressure route structurally dead. **E009: adversarial review of 6 claims.** **S2-E001: Proposition 3 sharpness audit ‚Äî Chebyshev on NS solutions is single improvable step.** **S2-E003: Universal formula beta = 1 + s/n across 9 model PDEs; Chebyshev NOT independently improvable (6 routes ruled out or circular); SQG success = drift structure, not Chebyshev; div-free level-set question RESOLVED by S2-E008 (constant field extremizer ‚Äî no improvement). S2-E004: Compensated compactness / commutator route CLOSED ‚Äî three-layer obstruction (no div-curl, commutator remainder dominance, CRW vacuous); SQG-NS structural gap; beta = 4/3 sharp within energy+Sobolev+CZ+Chebyshev class. S2-E002: DNS level-set distribution tails IC-dependent (TG p~10, Random p~8-9, ABC p~2.1 < 10/3); Chebyshev tightness ratios ~3-5x and k-independent (constant slack, not beta-improving). S2-E005: Frequency-localized De Giorgi via LP decomposition CLOSED ‚Äî Bernstein exchange rate 2^{3j/5} is dimensional, CZ is optimal frequency-by-frequency estimate, LP gives 5-10x worse bounds; paraproduct transition (resonance at low k, paraproduct at high k); direction 2 closed. S2-E006: Non-CZ pressure routes (IBP beta=1, H^1/BMO beta=4/3, CRW beta<=1) ‚Äî beta=4/3 TOOL-INDEPENDENT, locked to NS quadratic structure; CZ consolidation gain exactly 1/3; 12 published approaches surveyed, none beat 4/3; 3 remaining directions. S2-E007: Adversarial review confirms obstruction ‚Äî all 7 closures survive attack, 3 combination attacks fail, 15-paper lit search + Vasseur 2025 confirms no improvement, Tao 2016 supercritical connection; novel claim rankings (Claim 3 seven-route obstruction most significant); SDP formalization top priority. S2-E008: Chebyshev bound PROVABLY TIGHT for div-free fields ‚Äî constant field u=(c,0,0) achieves ratio->1; all 4 De Giorgi chain steps individually tight; beta = 4/3 SHARP (rigorous); div-free level-set question RESOLVED (no improvement); SDP unnecessary. far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole exploration-001: exact obstruction reconstruction ‚Äî harmonic `P_{k1}` is already favorable; the surviving far-field loophole is a decomposition mismatch, not literal `P_{k21}`; any live route must show an alternative near/far split makes the pressure factor `U_k`-dependent.** **29 entries.**
