execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-navier-stokes-learnings.md:38:- **The BKM advantage was 10‚Å∂-10¬π‚Åµ√ó larger than expected.** I designed the Phase 0 gate at T_BKM/T_Lad > 10, expecting 10-100√ó. The actual advantage is 10‚Å∑ to 10¬π‚Å∂. This is because the ŒΩ‚Åª¬≥ factor in the Ladyzhenskaya ODE is catastrophic at high Re. The lesson: when designing Phase 0 gates, set the threshold conservatively. Being surprised on the upside is fine; being surprised by a marginal result requires re-evaluation.
