execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/distinguish-typical-vs-worst-case-bounds.md:37:**NEW (vasseur-pressure E002):** When computing empirical analogues of analytical bounds, require the explorer to explicitly state what the empirical quantity IS and ISN'T relative to the analytical quantity. Vasseur-pressure E002: beta_eff (best-fit exponent from smooth DNS solutions) is fundamentally different from beta_p (worst-case exponent proved for all weak solutions). beta_eff < 4/3 does NOT mean the analytical bound is tight ‚Äî smooth solutions decay faster than worst-case regardless. The bottleneck exponent gamma is more directly comparable. Goal template addition: "State explicitly: what does this empirical quantity measure, and what analytical claim does it test? What would the empirical result need to show to provide evidence for/against the analytical conjecture?"
