execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:24:- **adversarial-check-between-phases.md** ‚Äî Run a lightweight adversarial check after Phase 2 (before Phase 3 computation begins); early reframing is more valuable than corrections after major compute is committed. *Updated (E008): upgraded to full standard-test adversarial exploration early.* **UPDATED (vasseur-pressure E009): timing refinement ‚Äî run adversarial AFTER key mechanism identified/tested but BEFORE extended tests. UPDATED (vasseur-pressure E010): adversarial -> targeted follow-up variant ‚Äî adversarial identifies weakest link, then a single targeted exploration definitively tests it (E010 confirmed E009's weakest-claim assessment via perturbed-ABC sweep).**
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:31:- **include-trivial-control-checks.md** ‚Äî NEW (thermal-time meta-003), UPDATED (vasseur-pressure E007): Every computation exploration should include one "should equal X by construction" check (different code path, limit case, or symmetry). The thermal-time E003 control check C_global = C_full (at machine zero for all Œª) confirmed that the 82.7% discrepancy was physical, not a bug. Cost: near zero. Payoff: immediate trust or bug detection. **NEW variants (E007):** known-answer validation at exact-solution conditions (t=0 Beltrami sanity check caught sign error propagated from prior code), and verify mathematical identity before building measurements (div(u_below) != 0 invalidated prescribed Lamb decomposition).
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:43:- **verify-counterexample-before-investigating.md** ‚Äî NEW (yang-mills-conjecture S002-meta-E007): When finding a potential counterexample, the FIRST priority is verifying it against the exact problem statement ‚Äî not investigating consequences. Check that the mathematical object being computed matches the conjecture's definition (representation, convention, normalization). A false counterexample can derail strategy. Protocol: stop ‚Üí re-read exact statement ‚Üí verify computation matches ‚Üí resolve ambiguity ‚Üí only then investigate.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:45:- **definition-extraction-gates-computation.md** ‚Äî NEW (vasseur-pressure E001): Before computation phases, run a definition-extraction exploration ("Phase 0") reading primary sources to verify the team's understanding of the target quantity. Prevents the most wasteful failure: computing the wrong thing due to incorrect mental model. Vasseur-pressure: team assumed beta = pressure integrability; Phase 0 revealed beta = De Giorgi recurrence exponent.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:46:- **sufficient-ic-diversity-for-outliers.md** ‚Äî NEW (vasseur-pressure E002): For measurement campaigns, use 5+ ICs covering different structural classes (symmetric/random, 2D-like/3D, special algebraic structure, low/high intermittency). Fewer ICs risk missing qualitatively different behavior. ABC (Beltrami) was the 5th IC and produced the most important finding (beta_eff = 1.01 vs 0.35-0.73 for others). Distinct from anticipate-symmetry-degeneracies (avoiding bad ICs) and require-independent-verification-baseline (checking same answer).
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:47:- **reconcile-notation-before-falsification.md** ‚Äî NEW (far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole meta-001): When a surviving lead is inherited across multiple vocabularies or decompositions, reconcile notation before falsification. Prevents testing the wrong object. Example: Vasseur's harmonic `P_{k1}` vs bad local `P_{k21}` vs later Wolf-style far/near split. Distinct from decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier (one proof's chain) and complementary to preload-context-from-prior-work (load context + verify compatibility).
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:48:- **decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier.md** ‚Äî NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E001): Always run a line-by-line proof reading + sharpness classification before attacking a mathematical barrier. Understanding the proof structure first prevents wasting budget on provably closed directions. S2-E001: narrowed 5 open Track B directions to 1, saving 3+ explorations. Deliver: step-by-step chain, sharpness classification, sensitivity table, free parameter catalog, attack surface narrowing. Distinct from definition-extraction-gates-computation (right quantity vs. right step) and gap-finding (literature landscape vs. single proof structure).
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:49:- **test-generalization-before-concluding.md** ‚Äî NEW (vasseur-pressure E010): When a mechanism is demonstrated for an exact special case (eigenstate, symmetry, exact solution), always test whether it extends to perturbations before treating it as a strategy conclusion. "Mechanism works for exact X" does NOT imply "mechanism works for near-X" ‚Äî eigenfunction properties can be structurally fragile. E010: Beltrami B_k = O(2^{-k}) destroyed by 1% perturbation. Design a perturbation sweep (eps = 0.01 to 0.50) before concluding. Distinct from verify-identity-generalization (proof identities, not empirical mechanisms) and adversarial-check (diagnostic, not treatment).
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:50:- **model-pde-comparison-for-mechanism-identification.md** ‚Äî NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E003): When investigating a mathematical barrier in a specific PDE, compare the barrier across structurally related model PDEs (different dimensions, dissipation orders, nonlinearities). Reveals whether the barrier is universal (same formula across PDEs ‚Äî attack the mechanism) or PDE-specific (study what the successful PDE has that the target lacks). S2-E003: comparing beta across Burgers/2DNS/SQG/MHD/fractional NS produced two major insights in one exploration ‚Äî universal formula beta = 1 + s/n AND SQG exception mechanism (drift structure, not Chebyshev). Protocol: identify barrier, list 4-6 model PDEs, compute barrier for each, tabulate, identify universal formula or systematic exceptions. Distinct from comparison-exploration-pattern (two approaches to one problem, not one approach across problems) and gap-finding (within one framework, not across).
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:51:- **test-improvability-before-pursuing-variations.md** ‚Äî NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E003): When a decomposition audit identifies a single target step as the potential weak link, the FIRST analytical exploration should test whether that target is independently improvable (i.e., improvement is possible without solving the entire original problem). If circular with the main problem, pivot immediately. S2-E003: 6 Chebyshev improvement routes all ruled out or circular in one exploration; improving L^{10/3} to L^4 Chebyshev requires H^{5/4} regularity (the Lions threshold = the original problem). Saved 3+ explorations on Lorentz/interpolation/support tricks. Protocol: enumerate improvement routes, classify each as (a) impossible, (b) insufficient, (c) circular, or (d) open; if all (a)/(b)/(c), target is not independently improvable ‚Äî pivot. Distinct from decomposition-audit (identifies target, not viability) and decisive-negative-pivot (dimensional analysis, not circularity detection).
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:52:- **extract-precise-obstruction-from-failed-route.md** ‚Äî NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E004): When a promising route fails, extract the PRECISE obstruction ‚Äî not just "it doesn't work." The precise failure point immediately suggests the next direction. S2-E004: three independent obstructions from the commutator route (no div-curl, remainder dominance, CRW vacuous) each generated specific next leads (frequency-localized De Giorgi, div-free approximation, unbounded-but-BMO multiplier). Protocol: identify all independent obstruction layers, state precise mathematical condition that fails, state what would need to change, rank resulting leads. Distinct from decisive-negative-pivot (decision to pivot vs. information extraction) and useful-failure-extracts-secondary-results (accidental findings vs. deliberate obstruction analysis).

