+# Meta Note: Exploration 002
+
+## What worked
+
+- Preloading the closure stack was essential. Without that, the intervention map would have drifted back into pressure rewrites, LP cleanup, or commutator reformulations that were already closed.
+- Tying the comparison table to Tao's literal gate chain `X_{1,n} -> X_{2,n} -> X_{3,n} -> X_{4,n} -> X_{1,n+1}` kept the exploration mechanism-level rather than slogan-level.
+- Treating pressure/Leray as a possible enforcement mechanism rather than automatically as the main candidate avoided re-opening the wrong route.
+
+## What to carry forward
+
+- When comparing an engineered toy mechanism to an exact PDE, the sharp question is often whether the toy subsystem can remain isolated inside the exact interaction network.
+- Distinguish "standalone candidate" from "mechanism enforcing another candidate." Pressure/Leray was not the candidate here; it was part of why coefficient rigidity and leakage may hold.
+- Tiny dynamically decisive variables are easy to overinterpret. The real question is whether exact dynamics can isolate their role, not whether small variables exist at all.
+
+## Execution note
+
+- The launched explorer initially drifted into over-broad repository search. Recovery worked once the task was pulled back to the table and the smallest live candidate set.
